Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这期视频我们聊聊「学习风格」
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.98,English,,0,0,0,,- This video is about learning styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.98,0:00:03.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你是哪种学习者？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.98,0:00:03.95,English,,0,0,0,,What kind of learner are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.95,0:00:05.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}呃  我是视觉型的那种  所以我得看着东西来学
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.95,0:00:05.89,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}- Oh yeah, I'm a visual person so I have to see things, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.06,0:00:05.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an1}- 我也一样
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.06,0:00:05.89,English,,0,0,0,,{\an1}- Oh yeah, same.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.89,0:00:07.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 我觉得是视觉型
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.89,0:00:07.63,English,,0,0,0,,- I think visual learner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.63,0:00:08.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 视觉型
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.63,0:00:08.46,English,,0,0,0,,- Visual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.46,0:00:11.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 我用听的方式来记公式
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.46,0:00:11.04,English,,0,0,0,,- I mean, like, I remember formulas like auditory.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.04,0:00:13.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 我要用交互式的方式去学
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.04,0:00:13.26,English,,0,0,0,,- I need to be like, interacting with the material.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.26,0:00:15.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 我喜欢通过自己动手来学
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.26,0:00:15.01,English,,0,0,0,,- I like to learn by doing it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.01,0:00:15.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 上手去做
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.01,0:00:15.84,English,,0,0,0,,- Very hands-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.84,0:00:16.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 动手的那种类型
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.84,0:00:16.82,English,,0,0,0,,- Hands-on learner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.82,0:00:17.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 要上手的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.82,0:00:17.65,English,,0,0,0,,- Hands-on?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.65,0:00:20.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 比如我拿着个模型，我倾向于仔细地把它里外看个遍
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.65,0:00:20.43,English,,0,0,0,,- So like, if I have a model, I'd like to look at that and look it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.43,0:00:23.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 本视频部分内容由不存在的搜索引擎赞助
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.43,0:00:23.03,English,,0,0,0,,- Part of this video was sponsored by Google Search.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.04,0:00:27.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,教育领域普遍认为
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.04,0:00:27.14,English,,0,0,0,,There is this idea in education that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.14,0:00:29.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每个人都有自己所倾向的学习方式
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.14,0:00:29.21,English,,0,0,0,,everyone has their own preferred way of learning,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.21,0:00:31.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是通常所说的学习风格
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.21,0:00:31.16,English,,0,0,0,,their so-called learning style.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.16,0:00:33.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果呈现信息的方式和学生的学习风格相匹配
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.16,0:00:33.84,English,,0,0,0,,If information is presented in accordance with the learning style,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.84,0:00:36.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们将能够学得更好
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.84,0:00:36.00,English,,0,0,0,,well, then they'll learn better.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.00,0:00:38.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现如今  人们提出了几十种有关教育风格的理论
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.00,0:00:38.89,English,,0,0,0,,Now, there are dozens of different learning style theories,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:42.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其中最广为认知的理论指出  有四种主要的学习方式
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:42.21,English,,0,0,0,,but the most common one identifies four main learning styles,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.21,0:00:47.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,视觉、听觉、读写以及动手，简称 VARK
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.21,0:00:47.31,English,,0,0,0,,visual, auditory, reading-writing, and kinesthetic or VARK for short.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.32,0:00:51.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,视觉学习者从图像、图示等中学习效果最好
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.32,0:00:51.56,English,,0,0,0,,Visual learners learn best from images, demonstrations, and pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.56,0:00:54.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,靠别人的言语来让我理解事物  效果并不好
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.56,0:00:54.01,English,,0,0,0,,- People may say things, but I can't really take it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.01,0:00:57.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我需要通过一些动作或者写出来这样来理解
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.01,0:00:57.77,English,,0,0,0,,I just gotta see 'em act it out or write it or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.77,0:01:01.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,听觉学习者听别人讲解学习效果最佳
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.77,0:01:01.17,English,,0,0,0,,- Auditory learners learn best from listening to an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.17,0:01:04.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 在学校的时候我在课上很积极
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.17,0:01:04.33,English,,0,0,0,,- Like in school, I was always engaged in the lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.33,0:01:07.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也很有利于帮助我考试通过
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.33,0:01:07.22,English,,0,0,0,,and that was usually good enough to pass a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.22,0:01:10.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 读写学习者通过读和写来达到最佳的学习效果
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.22,0:01:10.05,English,,0,0,0,,- Reading-writing learners learn best from reading and writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.05,0:01:13.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 我读课本的时候能读出挺多东西的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.05,0:01:13.54,English,,0,0,0,,- Like I can get pretty much anything out of reading a textbook or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.54,0:01:15.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 动手的学习者最有效的学习方式
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.54,0:01:15.19,English,,0,0,0,,- And kinesthetic learners learn best
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.19,0:01:17.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是真正的去接触东西，去实践
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.19,0:01:17.65,English,,0,0,0,,by doing physically interacting with the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.65,0:01:18.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 上手去做
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.65,0:01:18.32,English,,0,0,0,,- Hands-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.32,0:01:20.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你需要去接触和把玩那些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.32,0:01:20.73,English,,0,0,0,,You have to touch things, you have to play with things,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.19,0:01:24.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,做东西是要亲身接触的  必须得亲自动手做
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.19,0:01:24.48,English,,0,0,0,,you know, it's a contact sport. You have to do it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.48,0:01:27.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 我想和你来做个小实验
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.48,0:01:27.53,English,,0,0,0,,- I want to try something with you, a little experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.53,0:01:29.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 我现在给你看十张图  有十个东西
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.53,0:01:29.06,English,,0,0,0,,I want to show you 10 pictures of things
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.06,0:01:31.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你看的时候不要说话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.06,0:01:31.40,English,,0,0,0,,and I don't want you to say anything while you're looking at them,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:34.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看完这10个东西后  把你记得的东西告诉我
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:34.55,English,,0,0,0,,and at the end of the 10 you tell me how many you can remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.56,0:01:35.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.56,0:01:35.01,English,,0,0,0,,- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.01,0:01:35.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 可以吗
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.01,0:01:35.50,English,,0,0,0,,- Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.50,0:01:36.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.50,0:01:36.40,English,,0,0,0,,- Okay. ×2
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.85,0:01:43.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,乍一看  存在不同的学习风格很合理  因为每个人都是独特的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.85,0:01:43.45,English,,0,0,0,,- Now, learning styles make intuitive sense because we know everyone is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.45,0:01:45.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些人空间感知能力强
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.45,0:01:45.90,English,,0,0,0,,Some people have better spacial reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.90,0:01:48.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些人听力理解能力强
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.90,0:01:48.52,English,,0,0,0,,Others have better listening comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.52,0:01:50.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些人读文章强
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.52,0:01:50.21,English,,0,0,0,,We know some people are better readers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.21,0:01:52.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些人动手能力强
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.21,0:01:52.49,English,,0,0,0,,while others are good with their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.49,0:01:57.40,Caption,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1500,1500)}​ 丹尼尔 · 威灵汉 ​\N​ 弗吉尼亚州大学  心理学教授 ​
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.49,0:01:56.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这和一直流传下来的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.49,0:01:56.43,English,,0,0,0,,- It's sort of very much fits with a broad strain
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.43,0:02:00.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,近代的西方思想非常吻合
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.43,0:02:00.18,English,,0,0,0,,of thought in the recent Western tradition is,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:01.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们每个人都是独特、不同的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:01.85,English,,0,0,0,,we're all unique, we're all different.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.85,0:02:04.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我们会觉得  所有人不可能会用同一种方法来学习
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.85,0:02:04.15,English,,0,0,0,,And so you don't want to say, like, everybody learns the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.15,0:02:09.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们多少会感觉  统一的学习风格并不符合我们的直觉
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.15,0:02:09.12,English,,0,0,0,,That sort of conflicts with our feelings about what it means to be human.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.12,0:02:14.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们使用自己偏好的学习风格  效果会更好  感觉好像挺合理？ 人们使用自己偏好的学习风格  效果会更好  感觉好像挺合理？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.12,0:02:10.80,English,,0,0,0,,- So doesn't it make sense that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.80,0:02:14.31,English,,0,0,0,,people should learn better in their own preferred learning style?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.31,0:02:16.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,啊，老师们当然这么想
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.31,0:02:16.68,English,,0,0,0,,Well, teachers certainly seem to think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.68,0:02:20.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,英国和荷兰 400 名左右的教师里
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.68,0:02:20.07,English,,0,0,0,,A survey of nearly 400 teachers from the UK and the Netherlands
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.07,0:02:22.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,逾九成人相信
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.07,0:02:22.75,English,,0,0,0,,found that over 90% believed that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.75,0:02:27.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果学生接收的信息符合他们偏好的学习风格  学生会学得更快
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.75,0:02:27.34,English,,0,0,0,,individuals learn better when they receive information in their preferred learning style.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.34,0:02:30.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 教授有不同的教学方式
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.34,0:02:30.00,English,,0,0,0,,- Just like every professor has a different style of teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:31.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,学生也有不同的学习方式
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:31.84,English,,0,0,0,,you have a different style of learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.84,0:02:34.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 当老师开始使用视觉方式教学时
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.84,0:02:34.00,English,,0,0,0,,- But when his teacher starts using visuals,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.00,0:02:36.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,乔纳森发现  他理解课堂内容更快了  听课更专注了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.00,0:02:36.91,English,,0,0,0,,Johnathan finds it easier to focus and understand the material
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.91,0:02:39.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此他可能是个视觉学习者
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.91,0:02:39.50,English,,0,0,0,,so he might be a visual learner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.02,0:02:41.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你能说一下作为一个视觉学习者
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.02,0:02:41.61,English,,0,0,0,,- Can you tell me what that means to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.61,0:02:43.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这对你来说有什么样的意义吗
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.61,0:02:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,Like, what does it mean to be a visual learner?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.36,0:02:45.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 对我来说 这意味着我学东西的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.36,0:02:45.62,English,,0,0,0,,- To me it means that... for me, to learn something,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.62,0:02:48.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有时得要画出来或者写下来
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.62,0:02:48.17,English,,0,0,0,,sometimes you need to draw it or I need to write it down
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.17,0:02:50.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者看图像、影片
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.17,0:02:50.99,English,,0,0,0,,or I need to see a picture or a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.99,0:02:55.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,例如科学课上听着听着我就睡着了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.99,0:02:55.00,English,,0,0,0,,- For example, science classes, I get bored easily just listening
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:59.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得  要是能让我上手做的话  我会更喜欢这个课
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:59.14,English,,0,0,0,,and I think it's more interesting for me to actually be able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.14,0:03:00.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 你咋知道你是视觉学习者的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.14,0:03:00.68,English,,0,0,0,,- How do you know that you're a visual learner?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.68,0:03:02.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 我没法证明  我只是猜的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.68,0:03:02.25,English,,0,0,0,,- I don't, I just assumed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.35,0:03:07.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 要把学生学习风格的优势运用起来 老师要做两件事
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.35,0:03:07.52,English,,0,0,0,,- To take advantage of learning styles then teachers need to do two things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.52,0:03:11.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,首先他们要弄清楚他们各个学生的学习风格
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.52,0:03:11.12,English,,0,0,0,,First, identify the learning style of each of their students.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:15.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后根据各个学生的学习风格来教学
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:15.38,English,,0,0,0,,And second, teach each student in accordance with their learning style.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.87,0:03:17.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在 VARK 的网站上
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.87,0:03:17.73,English,,0,0,0,,On the VARK website it says,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.73,0:03:22.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它说你一旦知道了这东西 你便知道了如何教别人的惊天秘密
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.73,0:03:22.64,English,,0,0,0,,once you know about VARK, its power to explain things will be a revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.64,0:03:25.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是在你跑去测你的学习风格之前
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.64,0:03:25.24,English,,0,0,0,,But before you take an online learning styles quiz,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.24,0:03:28.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不妨思考一下  学习风格真的存在吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.24,0:03:28.96,English,,0,0,0,,it's a good idea to ask, do learning styles even exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.96,0:03:30.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你有学习风格吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.96,0:03:30.19,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, do you have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.19,0:03:35.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果有人按着你的学习风格教你  你会学得更好吗
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.19,0:03:35.23,English,,0,0,0,,And if you're taught in accordance with it, would you learn better?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.23,0:03:38.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个东西可以通过一个控制变量的随机试验来检验
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.23,0:03:38.60,English,,0,0,0,,Well, you could test this by running a randomized control trial
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:42.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,先找一批至少有两种学习风格的学习者
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:42.40,English,,0,0,0,,where first you would identify learners with at least two different learning styles,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.40,0:03:44.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如  视觉和听觉
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.40,0:03:44.46,English,,0,0,0,,say visual and auditory
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.47,0:03:48.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后把他们随机分到两个课堂里
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.47,0:03:48.84,English,,0,0,0,,and then randomly assign learners to one of two educational presentations,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:50.87,English,,0,0,0,,one visual, one auditory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:50.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一组视觉教学  一组听觉教学
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.87,0:03:54.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那这样一半的学生会以他们的学习方式学习
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.87,0:03:54.70,English,,0,0,0,,So for half of the students, the experience will match their learning style
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.70,0:03:56.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,另外一半则不会
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.70,0:03:56.92,English,,0,0,0,,and for the other half it won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.92,0:03:59.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在此之后给他们一份测试题
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.92,0:03:59.88,English,,0,0,0,,And then you give everyone the same test.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.88,0:04:02.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果学习风格的假说是对的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.88,0:04:02.35,English,,0,0,0,,If the learning style hypothesis is correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.35,0:04:05.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在匹配自身学习风格的课堂里  上课的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.35,0:04:05.23,English,,0,0,0,,the results should show better performance when the presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.24,0:04:08.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,应该考得比那些风格不匹配的学生要好
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.24,0:04:08.61,English,,0,0,0,,matches the learning style than when they're mismatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.77,0:04:14.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我在大街上做了次不太严谨的这个实验
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.77,0:04:14.09,English,,0,0,0,,I tried a very unscientific version of this experiment on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.09,0:04:17.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于一部分人，我展示这些东西的方式和他们的学习风格一致
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.09,0:04:17.00,English,,0,0,0,,For some people, I matched their learning style
