Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.40,0:05:29.93,English,,0,0,0,,because the presentation matched their preferred learning style
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.93,0:05:33.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是因为他们在记忆时运用了技巧
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.93,0:05:33.11,English,,0,0,0,,but because they employed a memory strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.11,0:05:36.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 你在给我看的时候我脑内就形成了一个顺序
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.11,0:05:36.35,English,,0,0,0,,- So as you were showing I was making an order in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.35,0:05:39.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,新加进来一个我就把它加到列表里
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.35,0:05:39.13,English,,0,0,0,,So as I saw more I would just add it to the list
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.13,0:05:41.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我回答的时候就会像把这个列表念出来一样
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.13,0:05:41.24,English,,0,0,0,,and I was repeating the list as I was looking at them
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.24,0:05:42.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以就挺轻松的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.24,0:05:42.41,English,,0,0,0,,so I could just say it out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.41,0:05:45.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 你记忆的时候用了什么特殊技巧吗
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.41,0:05:45.88,English,,0,0,0,,- Did you try a strategy while you were looking at those pictures?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:46.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}- 是
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:46.48,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}- Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.58,0:05:49.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我把它们连成了一个故事
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.58,0:05:49.54,English,,0,0,0,,So I guess I tried creating a story
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.54,0:05:52.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样记起来比这些零散的要轻松
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.54,0:05:52.66,English,,0,0,0,,'cause it's easier to remember a story than just individual objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.66,0:05:55.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我刚刚尝试把它串成故事
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.66,0:05:55.11,English,,0,0,0,,So I tried to tie it all into one story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.11,0:05:57.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然这不是太正经的依据了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.11,0:05:57.37,English,,0,0,0,,- This is all obviously anecdotal evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.37,0:06:01.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是类似的更严谨的研究已经有人做过了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.37,0:06:01.22,English,,0,0,0,,but rigorous studies like the one I outlined have been conducted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.22,0:06:04.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有项研究  对比的是图形学习者和文字学习者
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.22,0:06:04.79,English,,0,0,0,,For example, one looked at visualizers versus verbalizers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.79,0:06:07.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而非视觉、听觉学习者
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.79,0:06:07.21,English,,0,0,0,,instead of visual versus auditory learners.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.21,0:06:09.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一个基于计算机的测试
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.21,0:06:09.60,English,,0,0,0,,The study was computer-based,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.60,0:06:12.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,首先这些学生会回答一些问题
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.60,0:06:12.50,English,,0,0,0,,so first students' learning styles were assessed using questions like,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:17.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,例如你喜欢看原子的文字还是示意图的描述
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:17.44,English,,0,0,0,,would you rather read a paragraph or see a diagram describing an atom?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.44,0:06:20.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,研究者还整了一些复杂的介绍
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.44,0:06:20.47,English,,0,0,0,,The researchers also provided some challenging explanations
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.47,0:06:24.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,配上「图形解说」和「文字解说」的两个按钮
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.47,0:06:24.11,English,,0,0,0,,with two buttons, visual help or verbal help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.11,0:06:26.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,图形解说会放一个小动画
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.11,0:06:26.29,English,,0,0,0,,The visual one played a short animation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.29,0:06:29.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,文字解说则会弹出一段文字
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.29,0:06:29.67,English,,0,0,0,,whereas the verbal help gave a written explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.67,0:06:30.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,通过这些方式
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.67,0:06:30.86,English,,0,0,0,,From these measures combined,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.87,0:06:35.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,研究者将这些学生分成了图形和文字学习者两类
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.87,0:06:35.21,English,,0,0,0,,the researchers categorized the students as either visualizers or verbalizers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.21,0:06:37.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后将他们在一堂电路课里随机分配
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.21,0:06:37.47,English,,0,0,0,,and then the students were randomly assigned
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.47,0:06:42.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这堂课有文字和图像两种授课方式
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.47,0:06:42.11,English,,0,0,0,,to go through a text-based or picture-based lesson on electronics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.11,0:06:46.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当学生把指针悬停在关键词上时
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.11,0:06:46.52,English,,0,0,0,,When a student hovered their mouse over key words
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.52,0:06:48.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,文字授课方式的课堂将显示它的定义和解释
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.52,0:06:48.81,English,,0,0,0,,in the lesson in the text-based group, a definition and clarification came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.81,0:06:50.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而图像授课方式的课堂
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.81,0:06:50.01,English,,0,0,0,,But in the picture group,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:52.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,则是显示一个示意图
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:52.78,English,,0,0,0,,an annotated diagram was shown instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.78,0:06:56.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,上完课后  测试者发给学生一套测试题来检验学习情况
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.78,0:06:56.66,English,,0,0,0,,And after the lesson, the students did a test to assess their learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.66,0:07:00.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,学习方式符合自身学习风格的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.66,0:07:00.30,English,,0,0,0,,The students whose preferred learning style matched their instruction
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:05.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在测试中的发挥  并没有比学习方式不合自身风格的同学好
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:05.11,English,,0,0,0,,performed no better on the tests than those whose instruction was mismatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.11,0:07:09.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,测试者还在 61 个没受过大学教育的学生上做了同样的测试
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.11,0:07:09.25,English,,0,0,0,,The researchers ran the test again with 61 non-college-educated adults
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.25,0:07:11.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,结果是一致的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.25,0:07:11.60,English,,0,0,0,,and found exactly the same result.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.60,0:07:14.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是  学习风格是种「偏好」
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.60,0:07:14.13,English,,0,0,0,,But learning styles are a preference
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.13,0:07:17.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么  学生们的偏好有多固定呢
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.13,0:07:17.60,English,,0,0,0,,so how strongly do learners stick to their preference?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.60,0:07:20.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在 2018 年的一项研究中  在学期伊始
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.60,0:07:20.63,English,,0,0,0,,Well, in a 2018 study during the first week of semester,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.63,0:07:25.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,印第安纳州一所大学的 400 多名学生  填写了 VARK 调查问卷
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.63,0:07:25.51,English,,0,0,0,,over 400 students at a university in Indiana completed the VARK questionnaire
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.51,0:07:28.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,根据问卷得出的学习风格  他们被分为四大组
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.51,0:07:28.00,English,,0,0,0,,and they were classified according to their learning style.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.00,0:07:29.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到了学期结束时
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.00,0:07:29.32,English,,0,0,0,,Then at the end of the semester
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.32,0:07:32.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些学生又填写了实际学习方式的调查问卷
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.32,0:07:32.38,English,,0,0,0,,the same students completed a study strategy questionnaire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:35.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们在这个学期实际上是怎么学的呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:35.78,English,,0,0,0,,So how did they actually study during the term?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.78,0:07:37.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,占压倒性多数的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.78,0:07:37.99,English,,0,0,0,,Well, an overwhelming majority of students
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.99,0:07:42.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使用的学习策略反而与学习风格不匹配
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.99,0:07:42.58,English,,0,0,0,,used study strategies which were supposedly incompatible with their learning style,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.58,0:07:44.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而极少数使用了相符策略的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.58,0:07:44.49,English,,0,0,0,,and the minority of students who did
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.49,0:07:48.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在课程的考试中并没有与前者产生显著差异
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.49,0:07:48.76,English,,0,0,0,,did not perform significantly differently on the assessments in the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.76,0:07:52.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,视觉、听觉、读写、动手模型（即 VARK 模型）
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.76,0:07:52.29,English,,0,0,0,,The visual auditory reading-writing, kinesthetic or VARK model
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.29,0:07:56.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由新西兰的一位学校督学——尼尔・佛莱明提出
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.29,0:07:56.04,English,,0,0,0,,came about from Neil Fleming, a school inspector in New Zealand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.04,0:07:58.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他是这样描述 VARK 来由的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.04,0:07:58.29,English,,0,0,0,,Describing the origins of VARK he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:08:02.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我观察到的现象让我困惑  厉害的老师也有教不会的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:08:02.43,English,,0,0,0,,I was puzzled when I observed excellent teachers who did not reach some learners
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.43,0:08:04.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,较差的老师也有能教得会的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.43,0:08:04.16,English,,0,0,0,,and poor teachers who did.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.16,0:08:06.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我想试试去解决这一问题
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.16,0:08:06.29,English,,0,0,0,,I decided to try to solve this puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.29,0:08:09.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然  我观察到了不少缘由
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.29,0:08:09.49,English,,0,0,0,,There are, of course, many reasons for what I observed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.49,0:08:14.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我觉得有一个原因是最有说服力的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.49,0:08:14.08,English,,0,0,0,,But one topic that seemed to hold some magic, some explanatory power,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.08,0:08:17.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那就是「偏好的学习模式」或称「典型偏好」
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.08,0:08:17.80,English,,0,0,0,,was preferred modes of learning, modal preferences.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.80,0:08:20.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,VARK 因此而生
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.80,0:08:20.18,English,,0,0,0,,And thus, VARK was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.18,0:08:24.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原来  没有研究证明学生会天然的分成四个组别
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.18,0:08:24.91,English,,0,0,0,,There was no study that revealed students naturally cluster into four distinct groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.91,0:08:26.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是有什么魔法  或许能解释
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.91,0:08:26.66,English,,0,0,0,,Just some magic that might explain
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.66,0:08:29.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么有些老师能教得会学生  而有些不行
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.66,0:08:29.88,English,,0,0,0,,why some teachers can reach students while others can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.88,0:08:31.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但其原理是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.88,0:08:31.43,English,,0,0,0,,But how can this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.43,0:08:33.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们认可  有些人相对更擅长
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.43,0:08:33.70,English,,0,0,0,,If we accept that some people are more skilled at
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:38.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,处理、记忆某几类因素  比如图像或声音
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:38.65,English,,0,0,0,,interpreting and remembering certain kinds of stimuli than others like visual or auditory,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.65,0:08:43.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为何在学习或者回忆事物的测试中  显示不出差别呢
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.65,0:08:43.59,English,,0,0,0,,then why don't we see differences in learning or recall with different presentations?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.60,0:08:46.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是因为  其实人们需要记忆的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.60,0:08:46.48,English,,0,0,0,,Well, it's because what we actually want people to recall
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.48,0:08:51.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并不是图像的精确性质  亦非声音的音调和质量
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.48,0:08:51.01,English,,0,0,0,,is not the precise nature of the images or the pitch or quality of the sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.01,0:08:53.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要记的是各种表现形式背后的「实际含义」
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.01,0:08:53.21,English,,0,0,0,,It's the meaning behind the presentations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.21,0:08:57.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些任务必然需要使用某一类特定的表现形式
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.21,0:08:57.52,English,,0,0,0,,There are some tasks that obviously require the use of a particular modality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.52,0:09:01.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如说  学音乐肯定依赖于声音
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.52,0:09:01.18,English,,0,0,0,,Learning about music, for example, should have an auditory component.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:05.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,类似的  学地理肯定需要看地图
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:05.05,English,,0,0,0,,Similarly, learning about geography will involve looking at maps.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.05,0:09:09.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些人天生就比别人更擅长学习某类任务
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.05,0:09:09.31,English,,0,0,0,,And some people will have greater aptitude to learn one task over another.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.31,0:09:13.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如说  有绝对音感的人肯定更容易记住音乐中的音调
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.31,0:09:11.08,English,,0,0,0,,Someone with perfect pitch, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.09,0:09:13.83,English,,0,0,0,,will be better able to recall certain tones in music.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.83,0:09:18.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,视觉-空间推理能力强的人  能更准确地在地图上定位国家
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.83,0:09:15.82,English,,0,0,0,,Someone with excellent visual-spatial reasoning
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.82,0:09:18.87,English,,0,0,0,,will be better at learning the locations of countries on a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.87,0:09:24.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但学习风格理论宣称  这些偏好性不管学啥东西都是不变的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.87,0:09:20.93,English,,0,0,0,,But the claim of learning style theories is that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.93,0:09:24.79,English,,0,0,0,,these preferences will be consistent across learning domains.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.79,0:09:29.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有绝对音感的人  碰到一切声音信息时  都应该学得更快
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.79,0:09:29.36,English,,0,0,0,,The person with perfect pitch should learn everything better auditorily
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.36,0:09:31.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这很明显不合道理
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.36,0:09:31.70,English,,0,0,0,,but that is clearly not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.70,0:09:34.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大部分人学好地理靠的是地图
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.70,0:09:34.63,English,,0,0,0,,Most people will learn geography better with a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.94,0:09:39.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,专家审查了学习风格的文章后  一致认为
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.94,0:09:39.28,English,,0,0,0,,Review articles of learning styles consistently conclude
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.28,0:09:43.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尚没有显著的证据能证明学习风格真的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.28,0:09:43.02,English,,0,0,0,,there is no credible evidence that learning styles exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.03,0:09:45.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在 2009 年的审核中  研究者指出
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.03,0:09:45.42,English,,0,0,0,,In a 2009 review, the researchers note,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.42,0:09:54.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,学习风格论在教育界的流行  跟它缺乏可信证据的事实  形成了鲜明对比
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.42,0:09:48.10,English,,0,0,0,,the contrast between the enormous popularity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.10,0:09:50.63,English,,0,0,0,,of the learning styles approach within education
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.63,0:09:54.06,English,,0,0,0,,and the lack of credible evidence for its utility is,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.06,0:09:57.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们认为这很离谱  这样的现状让我们很不安
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.06,0:09:57.17,English,,0,0,0,,in our opinion, striking and disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.18,0:10:00.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要是对学生的学习风格进行分类有实际作用的话
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.18,0:10:00.61,English,,0,0,0,,If classification of students' learning styles has practical utility,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.61,0:10:02.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它还需要进一步的证据来证明
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.61,0:10:02.68,English,,0,0,0,,it remains to be demonstrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.68,0:10:06.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们本来期望的是  在遵循了相符的学习风格的情况下
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.68,0:10:06.14,English,,0,0,0,,- What we're expecting is, if your style was honored
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.14,0:10:10.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你应该比使用了相异学习风格的表现要更好
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.14,0:10:08.25,English,,0,0,0,,you're going to perform better than if
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.25,0:10:10.80,English,,0,0,0,,you had some experience that conflicted with your style.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.80,0:10:15.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们在这一点上看不到任何支持学习风格论的证据
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.80,0:10:15.59,English,,0,0,0,,And this is where we don't see any support for the learning styles theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:17.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们对学习风格论如此的深信不疑
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:17.58,English,,0,0,0,,- One of the reasons many people find learning styles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.58,0:10:21.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或许是因为他们一上来就相信了学习风格的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.58,0:10:21.72,English,,0,0,0,,so convincing is because they already believe it to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.72,0:10:25.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们可能已经相信自己是视觉学习者
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.72,0:10:25.14,English,,0,0,0,,For example, they might already think that they're a visual learner,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.14,0:10:29.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果老师给他们展示了一份图解  比如说自行车打气筒
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.14,0:10:29.00,English,,0,0,0,,and then when a teacher shows them a diagram of, say, a bike pump
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.00,0:10:30.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后学生一下子开窍了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.00,0:10:30.88,English,,0,0,0,,and suddenly the concept clicks,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:34.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们就认为  这恰好能作为证据  印证自己是个视觉学习着
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:34.31,English,,0,0,0,,well, they interpret this as evidence for their visual learning style.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.31,0:10:36.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你先入为主的认为学习方法是正确的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.31,0:10:36.76,English,,0,0,0,,- You already believe that learning styles is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.76,0:10:39.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当你从实践中获得经验时  你第一时间先想
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.76,0:10:39.50,English,,0,0,0,,When you have an experience the first thing you think is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.50,0:10:42.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它符不符合我的学习风格
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.50,0:10:42.20,English,,0,0,0,,is that in some way consistent with learning styles?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.20,0:10:43.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果符合  你就不再深入思考了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.20,0:10:43.76,English,,0,0,0,,And if it is, you don't think further.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:49.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那说不定是对任何人都有帮助的优质图解
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:45.00,English,,0,0,0,,- When in reality that diagram
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.00,0:10:49.09,English,,0,0,0,,might just be a great diagram that would have helped anyone learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.09,0:10:52.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当头脑中已经有了思维定势的框框  认为世界就是这样运行
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.09,0:10:52.23,English,,0,0,0,,When we already believe the world to be a certain way,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.23,0:10:55.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后把一切新的经验往框框里套
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.23,0:10:55.64,English,,0,0,0,,then we interpret new experiences to fit with those beliefs
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.64,0:10:57.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而忽略了这经验符不符合「框框」
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.64,0:10:57.68,English,,0,0,0,,whether they actually do or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.31,0:11:02.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，如果学习风格对学习并无帮助，那什么才有帮助呢
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.31,0:11:02.44,English,,0,0,0,,So if learning styles don't improve learning, then what does?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.44,0:11:04.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上  有大量文献支持的一个观点是
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.44,0:11:04.50,English,,0,0,0,,Well, there's a large body of literature that supports the claim that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.72,0:11:07.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使用多种感官形式来学习的效果会优于单一形式
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.72,0:11:07.33,English,,0,0,0,,everyone learns better with multimodal approaches
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.33,0:11:12.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同时展示文本和图像的效果要优于只展现其中一者
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.33,0:11:09.98,English,,0,0,0,,where words and pictures are presented together
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.98,0:11:12.60,English,,0,0,0,,rather than either words or pictures alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.60,0:11:15.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,接下来  文字是和图像一起展示的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.60,0:11:15.09,English,,0,0,0,,Now there's gonna be words as well as the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.09,0:11:16.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看看结果会不会更好一点
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.09,0:11:16.97,English,,0,0,0,,We're gonna see if this is any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.98,0:11:19.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种效应被称为「多媒体效应」
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.98,0:11:19.43,English,,0,0,0,,This is known as the multimedia effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.43,0:11:21.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它至少在一定程度上解释了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.43,0:11:21.36,English,,0,0,0,,and it explains in part, at least,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.36,0:11:26.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,拥有图像和旁白的视频  为什么能成为一种强大的学习工具
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.36,0:11:24.17,English,,0,0,0,,why videos can be such powerful tools for learning
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.17,0:11:26.92,English,,0,0,0,,when the narration complements the visuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.92,0:11:27.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,鸭子
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.92,0:11:27.60,English,,0,0,0,,- Duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.60,0:11:28.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}鸭子
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.60,0:11:28.14,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}- Duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.13,0:11:30.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,心
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.13,0:11:30.68,English,,0,0,0,,- Heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.68,0:11:31.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}心
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.68,0:11:31.23,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}- Heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.64,0:11:33.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在我的博士研究中我发现
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.64,0:11:33.28,English,,0,0,0,,- In my PhD research, I found
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.28,0:11:36.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在物理学入门的多媒体教学中
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.28,0:11:36.10,English,,0,0,0,,explicit discussion of misconceptions was essential
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.10,0:11:38.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对错误概念的明确讨论是至关重要的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.10,0:11:38.74,English,,0,0,0,,in multimedia teaching for introductory physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.74,0:11:39.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几个了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.74,0:11:39.49,English,,0,0,0,,- How many is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.49,0:11:40.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,六个
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.49,0:11:40.12,English,,0,0,0,,{\an1}- Six.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.12,0:11:41.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,六个，不错嘛
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.12,0:11:41.12,English,,0,0,0,,- Six, okay, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.12,0:11:43.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这好了一半呢
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.12,0:11:43.49,English,,0,0,0,,- That is a whole 50% better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.49,0:11:45.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你觉得这样更简单吗
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.49,0:11:45.05,English,,0,0,0,,Do you think that was easier?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:47.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 对，百分百更简单
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:47.93,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, yeah, 100%, 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.52,0:11:47.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 对，有了文字更简单，对
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.52,0:11:47.07,English,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, with the words, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.94,0:11:50.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,学习中最终极、最重要的特质
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.94,0:11:50.50,English,,0,0,0,,- Ultimately, the most important thing for learning
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:52.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不是呈现信息的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:52.91,English,,0,0,0,,is not the way the information is presented
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.91,0:11:55.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是学习者脑袋里有何过程
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.91,0:11:55.94,English,,0,0,0,,but what is happening inside the learner's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.94,0:11:59.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们学得最牢固的时候  是他们活跃地思考材料、
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.94,0:11:59.34,English,,0,0,0,,People learn best when they're actively thinking about the material,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.34,0:12:03.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,解决问题、或是想象不同变量的变化方式
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.34,0:12:03.91,English,,0,0,0,,solving problems or imagining what happens if different variables change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.92,0:12:06.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我之前聊过学习的最佳方式、为什么这方式最佳
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.92,0:12:06.29,English,,0,0,0,,I talked about how and why we learn best
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.29,0:12:09.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,快去康康我之前的视频「思考的科学」
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.29,0:12:09.59,English,,0,0,0,,in my video, "The Science of Thinking" so check that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.59,0:12:14.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,真相是  有许多教学方法已得到证据佐证  有助于学习
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.59,0:12:14.22,English,,0,0,0,,Now, the truth is, there are many evidence-based teaching methods that improve learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.22,0:12:17.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但学习风格论不能算在里面
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.22,0:12:17.72,English,,0,0,0,,Learning styles is just not one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.72,0:12:21.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,鉴于对学习风格广泛存在的误解
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.72,0:12:21.83,English,,0,0,0,,And it is likely, given the prevalence of the learning styles misconception
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.83,0:12:24.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它很可能实际上会让学习效果更差
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.83,0:12:24.21,English,,0,0,0,,that it actually makes learning worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.21,0:12:27.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的意思是  学习风格论给教师带来了不必要的担心
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.21,0:12:27.89,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, learning styles give teachers unnecessary things to worry about,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.89,0:12:32.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还导致一些学生不愿参与某些形式的教学
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.89,0:12:32.65,English,,0,0,0,,and they make some students reluctant to engage with certain types of instruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.65,0:12:36.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,浪费在学习风格和相关培训上的时间和金钱
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.65,0:12:36.02,English,,0,0,0,,And all the time and money spent on learning styles and related training
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.02,0:12:40.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,本可以更好地用于真正改善学习的措施上
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.02,0:12:40.18,English,,0,0,0,,could be better spent on interventions that actually improve learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.18,0:12:45.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你并不是什么视觉、听觉、动手学习者
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.18,0:12:45.64,English,,0,0,0,,You are not a visual learner nor an auditory learner nor a kinesthetic learner,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.65,0:12:50.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,更准确地说  你是依赖于所有感官的学习者  是上面的集合体
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.65,0:12:50.31,English,,0,0,0,,or more accurately, you are all these kinds of learner in one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.31,0:12:56.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最好的学习实践  应囊括了对同一事物的多种理解角度
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.31,0:12:52.95,English,,0,0,0,,The best learning experiences are those that involve
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.95,0:12:56.61,English,,0,0,0,,multiple different ways of understanding the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.62,0:13:03.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且最好的是  这样的策略不是对一部分人  而是对所有人都适用
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.62,0:13:03.43,English,,0,0,0,,And best of all, this strategy works not just for one subset of people but for everyone.
